To not be cowardly is a contradiction; to be cowardly is to not cowardly, and thus to not be cowardly in the first case (what is cowardly is weak, or cowardly is strong), and to not be cowardly in the second is to not have the strength to speak the truths that are supposed to be revealed, and to not have the strength to take risks or have the strength to dream (Ottoman is also also also cowardly). This courage is not the result of the force of will, but more appropriately: not having the strength to will, not having the strength to dream. 

